<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="jn1027a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="jn1" href="#jn1027">JN1: </a>  <a href="../../FF/unbs/jn1all.htm#jn1027a"> (NLI.2A) 27(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <p class="set">It was a beauty that I saw, <br>So pure, so perfect as the frame <br>Of all the universe was lame, <br>To that one figure could I draw, <br>Or give least line of it a law&mdash;</p> <p class="set">A skein of silk without a knot, <br>A fair march made without a halt, <br>A curious form without a fault, <br>A printed book without a blot, <br>All beauty and without a spot.</p> <p class="duup"> <u>Ben Johnson</u></p> <p class="duup"> &mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash; In his play &mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;</p> <p class="duup"> &ldquo;The New Inn&rdquo;</p> <p class="duup"> &mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;</p> </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: <cite>The Works of Ben Jonson</cite>, ed. William Gifford (London: Nicol, 1816), <a href="https://archive.org/details/worksofbenjonson05jonsuoft/page/410/mode/2up" target="_blank">Vol. V: &ldquo;The New Inn&rdquo; Act IV. Scene III, p. 411</a>.</mm> </dd></dl>
